news.title: Jaipur development body razes four illegal colonies
news.para: While two of this colonies fall under jurisdiction of zone 14 of the civic, the rest two were coming up at the ecological zone under the jurisdiction of zone 10.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government waives interest on property tax dues
news.para: Y Srilakshmi said the decision to waive the interest on the old dues was taken as a one-time incentive to provide relief to all those who could not pay the taxes in the last two years due to the lockdowns following the outbreak of Covid-19.

news.title: About 9.22 lakh families left out of PMAY: Rajasthan rural development minister
news.para: He said that the central government is being urged to upload these deprived families on Awas Plus. He said that there was no negligence on the part of the officers and employees of the department in this matter.

news.title: Enforcement directorate searches three sites to spot PMAY scam
news.para: The ED has registered a money laundering case against the builders based on an FIR registered at Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar city police station on February 23.

news.title: Noida authority sets up a panel to inspect STPs in societies
news.para: According to officials, a Delhi-based company has been hired to inspect STPs and ensure that they are properly functioning. The team will be provided space in the Noida Authority office.

news.title: Haryana RERA directs Splendor Landbase to pay fine with interest to home buyers
news.para: The authority also set aside a unit cancellation notice issued by the builder — Splendor Landbase Limited — on February 7.

news.title: Bombay HC restrains Avarsekar Realty from selling unsold flats across projects
news.para: Bombay high court recently restrained a builder, Avarsekar Realty Pvt Ltd, from selling any of its unsold flats as on date in a proposed plush 42-storey highrise at Mahim and its other projects till further orders.

news.title: Colliers India's CEO Ramesh Nair resigns
news.para: According to sources, Nair resigned as Colliers India CEO on Friday with immediate effect to pursue external opportunities. He was also Managing Director, Market Development for Asia, at Colliers.

news.title: WeWork reaches deals to cut debt, extend maturities
news.para: Last month, WeWork forecast weak current-quarter revenue, after having announced moves to cut 300 jobs and exit 40 underperforming U.S. locations in a move aimed at curbing its real-estate footprint.

news.title: In low-wage Portugal, Europe's housing crisis bites deep
news.para: The 57-year-old nursing home carer earns less than 800 euros ($845) a month, as do about a fourth of the country's workforce. For the last decade, she got by because she's been paying just 300 euros a month for her one-bedroom apartment in an undistinguished Lisbon neighborhood.

news.title: Maharashtra government revises guidelines for houses built, allotted by MHADA
news.para: As per the new guidelines, the apartments under MIG category will now be spread over up to 968 sq ft as against earlier permitted space of 1,722 sq ft. For HIG category, the carpet area has been increased from the limit of 2,152 sq ft to any configurations above 968 sq ft now.

news.title: MahaRERA issues notices to 14 projects for advertising without registration number
news.para: The regulator has asked all these projects to present their case within 7 days from the date of notice. The errors are expected to be rectified within the prescribed period and penal action will be taken against the developers that fail to respond appropriately.

news.title: Four years on, DDA finds two land parcels eligible to develop under land pooling policy
news.para: A DDA official confirmed receiving consensus on or expression of interest in pooling their holdings from landowners in Zone P-II, Sector 8B of the policy.

news.title: Two commercial buildings in Madurai with property tax arrears sealed
news.para: The first building is situated in ward 72 of zone V on Thiruparankundram Road and is owned by three people. The owners did not pay property tax since 2014-15 and the arrears amounted to 5.7 lakh for the last nine years.

news.title: Draft master plan for Delhi-2041 likely to be notified by March-end
news.para: ​The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) had earlier this month approved the draft master plan with Lt Governor VK Saxena highlighting its thrust for inclusive development, sustainability and innovative interventions such as transit-oriented development hubs, land pooling, heritage and Yamuna rejuvenation, and regeneration of the city.
